A Cylindropuntia californica is a species of cactus native to California.
It has a cylindrical stem and tall, spiny branches that grow upward.
The stem is greenish-gray and covered in small, barbed spines.
The branches are green and also covered in spines, which are longer and stronger on the younger branches.
The cactus blooms in the spring with small, yellow flowers.
It can be found in desert and coastal areas of California, as well as in rocky soil and chaparral.
Cylindropuntia californica is an important element of the local desert ecosystem, providing food and shelter for a variety of animals.
